Package: m3
Type: Package
Title: Multimodal, Multi-Batch, Condition-Aware Single-Cell Modelling
Version: 0.3.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Sichang", "Ding", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "usyddsc@gmail.com"))
Description: R interface to m3, a multimodal (RNA, ADT, ATAC), multi-batch,
    condition-aware single-cell model. Trains an integration variational
    autoencoder for batch-corrected, condition-disentangled cell embeddings and,
    on top of it, an adversarial donor-level disease predictor; it also explains
    predictions by end-to-end integrated gradients and augments cohorts with
    synthetic donors and cells. The PyTorch implementation (the 'm3-sc' Python package)
    is bundled and driven via 'reticulate' inside a 'basilisk'-managed environment, operating on SingleCellExperiment and
    MultiAssayExperiment objects and returning results as objects. Numerics are
    identical to the Python package for a given seed, device and library
    versions.
